12/06/2006
LUXEMBOURG -- Croatia and the EU were due to begin talks Monday (12 June) on the first of the 35 chapters of the acquis -- science and research -- in Luxembourg. Local media described this chapter as comparatively easy, adding talks might be completed in a day.
In other news, Croatian Foreign Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic visted Andorra on Sunday for talks with counterpart Juli Minoves. The focus was primarily on economic co-operation. Afterwards, officials said Andorra is very interested in investing in Croatia's tourism sector. (HRT, Vjesnik - 12/06/06; HINA - 09/06/06)
